# Quick Reference - Project Rules

One-line rules for quick lookup. See detailed files for explanations.

## Codegen
- Run `dart run build_runner build -d` after codegen changes
- Never commit `*.g.dart`, `*.freezed.dart`, `*.gr.dart`, `_g/`, `di.config.dart`
- Use Freezed for all domain entities and BLoC states
- Use extension types to wrap Ferry GraphQL types
- Router must be `@singleton` for Injectable

## Architecture
- Dependencies flow inward: UI â†’ Data â†’ Domain (never reverse)
- Domain layer has NO dependencies on outer layers
- Repositories return domain entities, never Ferry types or Drift models
- Use cases orchestrate business logic, repositories handle data access
- Features are independent modules with data/domain/ui layers

## Injectable
- `@singleton` for use cases, global BLoC, services
- `@lazySingleton` for repositories, feature-specific services
- `@injectable` for regular factories
- Use `@module` abstract class for DI modules (providers, database, etc.)
- Use `@InjectableInit()` on `configureDependencies` function
- Use `order` parameter: 1 (Data) â†’ 2 (Domain) â†’ 3 (App) â†’ 4 (UI)
- Constructor injection preferred, `GetIt.I<>()` acceptable in BLoC
- Use `@disposeMethod` for BLoC cleanup methods

## Freezed
- All domain entities use `@freezed`
- States extend `StateBase` and use Freezed
- Use `copyWith()` for immutable updates, never mutate directly
- Add `const ClassName._();` for custom methods
- Use `@Default()` for optional fields

## Ferry & GraphQL
- Write queries in `.graphql` files
- Use `GQueryNameReq()` for requests
- Access via `r.dataOrThrow(label: 'Label').field`
- Convert Ferry types â†’ entities via extension type `toEntity()`
- Never expose Ferry types outside data layer

## Repositories
- Return domain entities only
- Use `@lazySingleton` (or `@singleton` if needed)
- Extend `RemoteRepository` base for common patterns
- Separate local vs remote when needed
- All repos have mock implementations in `mock/` directory

## BLoC/Cubit
- States extend `StateBase` with `StateStatus` sealed class
- Use Freezed for state immutability
- Prefer use cases over direct repository access
- Use `copyWith()` to update state
- Pattern match on `StateStatus` for status checks

## Exceptions
- Server: `ExceptionBase` with hierarchical codes (code spaces: 1000, 1100, 1200...)
- Client: `LocalizableException` with `toEn`/`toRu` for user-facing errors
- Use sealed classes for exception types
- Domain exceptions in domain layer, feature exceptions in feature domain

## State Management
- `StateBase` with `StateStatus` sealed class
- Status: `StateIsSuccess`, `StateIsLoading`, `StateHasError`, `StateIsNavigating`, `StateIsMessaging`
- Pattern match with `is` checks
- Localizable messages in `StateIsMessaging`

## Platform Abstraction
- Use conditional exports: `export 'native.dart' if (dart.library.js_interop) 'web.dart';`
- Base abstraction required, platform-specific implementations
- Pattern: `*_base.dart`, `*_native.dart`, `*_web.dart`

## Environment
- All config via `Env` class, never hardcode
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Support `Env.dev()`, `Env.prod()`, `Env.test()`
- Env is `@singleton` and injected everywhere

## Testing
- Mocks use `@Injectable(as: RealType, env: [Environment.test])`
- Mocks in `data/repository/mock/` directory
- Mock data in `mock/data/` subdirectory
- Mocks implement full repository interface

## File Naming
- Screens: `*_screen.dart` (triggers Auto Route)
- States: `*_state.dart` (use Freezed)
- Repositories: `*_repository.dart` (use Injectable)
- Models: `*_model.dart` (extension types)
- GraphQL: `*.graphql` in `data/gql/`

## Auto Route
- Annotate screens: `@RoutePage()`
- Screens implement `AutoRouteWrapper` for BLoC setup
- Use `wrappedRoute()` to provide BLoC/Cubit before build
- Use `@PathParam('id')` and `@QueryParam('key')` for parameters
- Register in `root_router.dart` with `AutoRoute(page: MyRoute.page)`
- Router class must be `@singleton`

## Sealed Classes
- Use for closed type hierarchies (`StateStatus`, `ExceptionCodes`, `RepositoryEvent`)
- Prefer sealed over abstract for fixed sets
- Enable exhaustive pattern matching

## Extension Types
- Use for Ferry model wrappers (zero-cost)
- Implement `toEntity()` conversion method
- Keep wrappers thin

## Factory Methods
- Use `@FactoryMethod(preResolve: true)` for async initialization
- Keep factory methods focused
- Document initialization requirements

## Monorepo
- Shared domain in `lib/` (root package)
- Packages: `client/`, `server/`, `widgetbook/`
- Packages depend on root, not each other
- Independent versioning per package

## Constants & Utilities
- Use `k*` prefix for constants (kPathHome, kPaddingSmallH, kSpacingMedium)
- Define in `consts.dart`, export from root package
- Use `commonScreenBlocListener` for standard BLoC state handling (navigation, messaging, errors)
- Constants: `kPadding*`, `kSpacing*`, `kPath*`, `kQuery*`

## Screen Patterns
- Implement `AutoRouteWrapper` interface
- Use `wrappedRoute()` to wrap with `BlocProvider`/`MultiBlocProvider`
- Use `commonScreenBlocListener` in `BlocListener` for standard behavior
- Access BLoC via `GetIt.I<>()` or `context.read<>()` in build method

## Rule Maintenance
- If you observe significant architectural patterns in the codebase that contradict these rules, notify the user
- Suggest updating `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files when patterns diverge consistently
- Examples: new codegen tools, different layer structure, alternative state management patterns
- When suggesting updates, provide specific examples of the divergence found
